## 7. Ethical Considerations

> Bias risks, informed consent, privacy, potential harms, equity implications.
> Does this system reproduce or amplify existing disparities? Who bears the
> consequences when it fails?

[In terms of bias and equity, limited cultural awareness may lead to systematic exclusion of certain ethnic dietary practices. For privacy and data usage, User data (household size, food habits, budget) is sensitive and must be:

Collected with informed consent
Stored securely
Not shared without transparency

Potential Harms
Inaccurate recommendations could:
Lead to nutritional deficiencies
Suggest impractical foods (unavailable or culturally inappropriate)
Over-reliance on the system may reduce individual autonomy or critical decision-making

Responsibility
Failures disproportionately impact already vulnerable populations (low-income families)
Developers and deploying institutions bear responsibility for:
Monitoring harm
Updating the system
Providing fallback support
